			<body><div id="65--on-shermans-men">
				<pb facs="/images/battle-pieces-v1/battle-pieces-i-0182.jpg"/>
				<head type="main">
				<hi rend="italic">On Sherman&apos;s Men</hi>
				</head>
				<head type="sub-head"><hi rend="italic">who fell in the Assault of Kenesaw Mountain, Georgia.</hi>
				</head>
<lb/>
<lg>
<l n="1"><hi rend="smallcaps">They</hi> said that Fame her clarion dropped</l>
<l rend="2em">Because great deeds were done no more—</l>
<l>That even Duty knew no shining ends,</l>
<l>And Glory—&apos;twas a fallen star!</l>
<l rend="2em">But battle can heroes and bards restore.</l>
<l rend="6em">Nay, look at Kenesaw:</l>
<l>Perils the mailed ones never knew</l>
<l>Are lightly braved by the ragged coats of blue,</l>
<l>And gentler hearts are bared to deadlier war.</l>
</lg>
</div></body>
